<item>
            <title>[WICKET-3766] Strings#escapeMarkup() creates invalid XML for control characters</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/WICKET-3766</link>
                <project id="12310561" key="WICKET">Wicket</project>
                    <description>&lt;p&gt;Most C0 control characters are invalid in XML:&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;  &lt;a href=&quot;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Valid_characters_in_XML&quot; class=&quot;external-link&quot; target=&quot;_blank&quot; rel=&quot;nofollow noopener&quot;&gt;http://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Valid_characters_in_XML&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Besides 0x09, 0x0a and 0x0d all other control characters below 0x20 have to be escaped, see attached patch.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently model objects containing these characters and being rendered (e.g. via labels) will lead to Ajax response failures.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
