                            <comment id="13043266" author="svenmeier" created="Fri, 3 Jun 2011 09:37:01 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;escaping control characters&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13043267" author="mgrigorov" created="Fri, 3 Jun 2011 09:44:36 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;This is fixed in trunk several months ago. It wasn&apos;t ported to 1.4.x to not compromise its stability. I guess it proved to be stable and can be ported now.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13043287" author="svenmeier" created="Fri, 3 Jun 2011 10:34:45 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, I wasn&apos;t aware of this change in 1.5. Please backport it to 1.4.x.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;BTW the encoding is a little too strict: 0x09, 0x0a and 0x0d need not to be encoded. IMHO it would be nicer to humans to read the markup if they stayed like they are, i.e. not encoded.&lt;/p&gt;</comment>
                            <comment id="13043288" author="svenmeier" created="Fri, 3 Jun 2011 10:34:46 +0000"  >&lt;p&gt;Sorry, I wasn&apos;t aware of this change in 1.5. Please backport it to 1.4.x.&lt;/p&gt;

